Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of the Ternary Mixtures 2-Methyl-1-propanol (or 2-Methyl-2-propanol) + N-Hexane + 1-Chlorobutane at 298.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of the ternary mixtures 2-methyl-1-propanol (or 2-methyl-2-propanol) + n-hexane  + 1-chlorobutane have been measured at atmospheric pressure and 298.15 K. Excess molar volumes and  viscosity deviations for the ternary mixtures were calculated from experimental data and fitted by the Cibulka  equation. These properties have been analyzed taking into account the molecular interactions.
